Gillard sworn in as Prime Minister
Julia Gillard has been sworn in as Prime Minister at Government House in Canberra.
Australiaâ€™s first elected female leader, Ms Gillard was joined by partner Tim Mathieson and some of her frontbench colleagues including Treasurer Wayne Swan and his wife Kim.
Ms Gillard signed a document and swore allegiance to the Queen.
All ministers - including Defence Minister Stephen Smith, Treasurer Wayne Swan and Foreign Affairs Minister Kevin Rudd - and parliamentary secretaries have now been sworn in. After a group photo on the steps of Government House the group will adjourn for afternoon tea with Governor-General Quentin Bryce.